Instructions:

1. Create a "photos" folder in your root directory (where your HTML file is located)
2. Name your photos exactly as specified in the src attributes:
   · fleshy-fruits-type-a.jpg
   · dry-dehiscent-type-b.jpg
   · dry-indehiscent-type-c.jpg
   · serotinous-fruits.jpg
   · legume-pods.jpg
   · pole-pruner.jpg
   · cleaning-sieves.jpg
   · field-recording.jpg
   · seed-drying.jpg
   · seed-storage.jpg
   · viability-testing.jpg
   · gps-navigation.jpg
3. Supported image formats: You can use .jpg, .png, or .webp. Just update the file extension in the src attribute accordingly.
4. Fallback system: If an image is missing, the code automatically shows the original gradient placeholder with an icon, so your gallery will never look broken.
5. Photo tips:
   · Use landscape-oriented photos (they'll fit better in the 180px height)
   · Keep file sizes reasonable (under 500KB per image for fast loading)
   · Ensure good lighting and clear subject focus

The gallery will now display your actual photos when they exist in the photos folder, and gracefully fall back to the gradient placeholders if any images are missing.
